flags &= ~(option4 | option5); // turn options 4 and 5 offTo flip bit states, we usebitwise XOR:flags ^= option4; // flip option4 from on to off, or vice versa
flags ^= (option4 | option5); // flip options 4 and 5Quiz timeQuestion #1Do not usestd::bitsetin this quiz. We’re only usingstd::bitsetfor printing.Given the following program:#include <bitset>
